1.text: Offer dog walking or start a pet-sitting business.

2.text: Babysit for extra cash if you’re good with children.

3.text: Become a tutor if you’re very knowledgeable in a subject.

5.text: Complete errands or tasks for the elderly.

6.text: Find odd jobs online for extra cash.

7.text: Make a website or start a blog.

8.text: Become a freelancer in an area where you have expertise.

9.text: Complete online surveys for extra cash or gift cards.

10.text: Sell items you aren’t using any more.

11.text: Flip clothes and accessories from thrift stores or yard sales in online auctions.

12.text: Hunt for under-priced used books that you can sell online.

13.text: Try flipping houses if you have experience with making home repairs.

14.text: Sell handmade crafts or jewelry through an online shop or at local events.

15.text: Become a freelance photographer and sell photos online.

16.text: Refinish old furniture from thrift stores, yard sales, or online ads.
